The celebration of my Grandma Nook. From Ashes to Ashes, dust to dust. As much as we wished for you to be here for you 80th bday next month.. or that day when my new born children would enter this world and I could have the opportunity to place them in your arms.. you returned home. The Queen Matriarch. Has joined her mother, my Great Grandma, and all of her siblings.  I know that through this life, you will guide us.  Along with our Ancestors. Our family will be a Union together because we know that’s what you wanted.  I will miss your excited face and cheerful energy whenever I would return home from Argentina. I loved this Grand Woman so much 🥹😇. I will love you and cherish your graceful presence, cheerful smile, your realness, your authenticity, and all the memories forever. Thank you my heavenly, angel.  My life shall change for the better. There’s an even greater purpose hidden within the message of life and the return. Thank you for all of the condolences received from friends and family. May God bless you and your family. Hug them tight next time you see them. 🤞🏿 love and love only.  She’s really not coming back this time 😔. Until next time.

When I’m in the studio working with an artist, I always challenge them to deliver and perform to their best vocal ability. Sometimes you have to push them, and some people just naturally get it. It’s not easy to record or learn melodies, runs, and cadence.  Also, if you always record with autotune, try to record your vocals dry. Connect with your real voice.  Eventually, you will start to sound like your own signature version of autotune. I love producing vocals.  This kid got it!  #vocalproduction #production #mastery

Imagine being the one that is trying to network and you approach an artist like Ginuwine talkin bout “let’s get in the studio”. 😅 That’s why It’s better to connect off something genuine. Pun intended ha.  He ain’t even let Timbo in the studio unless necessary.  But Iike he said (to an extent). I prefer the stage > studio. Even though I been locked in 🔐And when I record music it’s usually dolo, or with specific artists and maybe someone affiliated. If u know me.. I used to always have a selective collection of people around during this process.  Say for an example, if I’m making a club record, or an r&b record. I might invite some tasteful women, or my homegirls to the studio to create an experience or the allure while I create .  Sometimes the presence, conversations, and energy helps translate into vibe and lyrics for a song. It wasn’t rare to leave the club and rally the entire VIP section to come back to the crib studio and make hits with that real club energy. Literally how we made 2On). But Frfr since post pandemic, I’ve found more liberation creatively and higher productivity when I write and/or record songs myself and not with so many others present during the process.
